8.21	Transport_and_General_Workers_Union	Transport and General Workers' Union	The Transport and General Workers' Union, also known as the TGWU and the T&amp;G, was one of the largest general trade unions in the United Kingdom and Ireland - where it was known as the Amalgamated Transport and General Workers' Union - with 900,000 members (and was once the largest trade union in the world). It was founded in 1922, and its final general secretary was Tony Woodley.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/e/e9/TGWU_logo.png
